```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "nodes": 1,
      "tasks": 1,
      "partition": "p0",
      "time": "08:00:00",
      "cpus_per_task": 8,
      "memory": "32G",
      "gpus": 1,
      "qos": "basic"
    },
    "software_requirements": {
      "cuda": "cuda-11.8.0",
      "python": "3.9",
      "libraries": [
        "huggingface",
        "pip"
      ]
    },
    "environment_variables": {
      "CACHE_DIR": "/nfs/scratch/students/$USER/.cache",
      "PIP_CACHE_DIR": "/nfs/scratch/students/$USER/.cache",
      "TRANSFORMERS_CACHE": "/nfs/scratch/students/$USER/.cache",
      "HF_HOME": "/nfs/scratch/students/$USER/.cache",
      "LD_LIBRARY_PATH": "/nfs/tools/spack/v0.21.0/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu20.04-zen2/gcc-9.4.0/cuda-11.8.0-y3u5n3kohg7mgnff4loe6t2pz6awb7ck/lib64/:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH",
      "PATH": "/nfs/tools/spack/v0.21.0/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu20.04-zen2/gcc-9.4.0/cuda-11.8.0-y3u5n3kohg7mgnff4loe6t2pz6awb7ck/bin/:$PATH"
    },
    "execution": {
      "command": "srun python /home/$(whoami)/api/Controller.py"
    }
  }
}
```

This script uses the **SLURM** workload manager to submit a job to a cluster. It defines resource requirements like number of nodes, tasks, partition, time limit, CPUs per task, memory, GPUs, and QoS. The script also sets up environment variables related to cache directories for Huggingface and PIP packages and sets the PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH for CUDA. Finally, it runs the "Controller.py" Python script within the specified environment.
